            <title>[ENTESB-3265] Installing patch on Fuse with activemq slave does not work</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-3265</link>
                <project id="12314570" key="ENTESB">JBoss Fuse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After applying patch on Fuse where activemq is running slave mode (shared filesystem master/slave) the patch is not applied correctly and you are unable to connect to fuse (both ./bin/client script and hawtio). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Connection through client ouputs: Failed to get the session.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Connection through hawtio outputs: &lt;br/&gt;
HTTP ERROR: 404&lt;br/&gt;
Problem accessing /hawtio/index.html. Reason:&lt;br/&gt;
Not Found&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the log file you can see that activemq is still trying to obtain lock. You are also unable to stop Fuse through stop script. After killing fuse and starting again client script still not works.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;two RHEL 7 on openstack with Fuse (no fabric) where activemq is configured as  shared filesystem (NFS) master/slave&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
